This role offers the opportunity to make a tangible, firm-wide impact, with real ownership to take responsibility for solutions and directly influence how technology is used across the organization. It spans the full lifecycle from concept and architectural design through to hands-on delivery and operationalization,
with a strong focus on building reusable, enterprise-grade capabilities.


The Solution Architect will play a key role in enabling business-critical initiatives and in driving the smart, sustainable adoption of technology to deliver measurable business value at scale, increased efficiency, and long-term evolution of our architectural and technology landscape.


The key tasks include:

Design, implement, and continuously evolve the firm’s software and technology landscape, applying deep expertise in key enabling technologies such as AI, cloud, and shared platforms. Actively guide their effective adoption across projects and business lines in close collaboration with internal teams, partners, and stakeholders;

Take end-to-end ownership of complex initiatives, being accountable for architectural and technology decisions and driving them through to successful, scalable, and sustainable implementation and adoption;

Define and drive the technical enterprise AI strategy and adoption of shared, scalable platforms, ensuring solutions are designed for reliability, reusability, and long-term impact;

Continuously explore and assess emerging technologies, tools, and architectural approaches, identifying opportunities to drive innovation, enhance efficiency, and enable scalable adoption of strategic capabilities;

Design and drive technical solutions that enable integration, optimization, and automation of business processes, working closely with business and platform management;

Co-steer the demand and prioritization process together with other Solution Architects and Business Owners, ensuring alignment with the target architecture, technology strategy, and business value objectives.

Requirements

Degree in Computer Science, or a related field (Master’s degree preferred);

Proven experience as a Senior Solution Architect and/or Lead Software Engineer, with a strong track record of hands-on design and delivery of enterprise-scale software ecosystems;

Demonstrated, practical expertise in key enabling technologies such as AI, cloud architecture, and shared platforms, including experience implementing and scaling solutions in complex enterprise environments;

Deep understanding of modern software development lifecycles and enterprise engineering practices, including architecture governance, DevOps, CI/CD, QA, and operational readiness;

Strong hands-on mindset combined with a proactive curiosity to learn, experiment, and explore new technologies, particularly in fast-evolving areas such as AI and automation;

Excellent collaboration and stakeholder management skills, with the ability to work effectively across business lines and influence senior stakeholders to drive aligned, firm-wide outcomes;

Clear and confident communicator, able to translate complex technical concepts into concise, audience-appropriate messages for both technical and non-technical stakeholders;

Experience in financial services and/or asset management is an advantage;

Excellent English oral and written communication skills; German is a plus.

What you can expect

We provide modern working conditions, including work-from-home options, flexible hours and a home office allowance to ensure staff members have a work environment equipped with the latest technology;

A diverse culture founded on mutual respect, teamwork and appreciation awaits you at LGT Capital Partners. We go the extra mile to generate impact;

We empower and invest in you: your professional development and personal growth are our priorities. We offer various internal and external training opportunities that are aligned with your ambitions and our business needs. If you are interested, you can also enhance your German or English language skills;

We are proud to be owned by the Princely Family of Liechtenstein and our company is inspired by its entrepreneurial spirit;

Commitment to ESG: our approach to business is influenced by the Princely Family’s long-term perspective. Sustainability is key for us and has shaped our actions since 2002;

You benefit from favorable terms and conditions if you wish to participate in LGT Capital Partners’ investment programs or to use LGT banking products and services.
